sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64040
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a variant of the pCASP secretion circuit with the sicA chaperone and the sipC secretion signal.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is comprised of parts taken from Salmonella LT2 Genomic DNA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with biobrick standard assembly compatibility in mind, it might contain scar sequence cutsites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64023
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the 167 amino acid secretion signal for the sipC protein in the Salmonella Type III Secretion System. This secretion signal can be fused to proteins of interest and will direct secretion to the extracellular space via the type III secretion apparatus. For secretion at high titer co-expression of the sicA chaperone protein (BBa_J64021) is required.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with compliance to biobricks standard assembly in mind.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64024
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the natural RBS from the sipC protein in Salmonella Type III Secretion.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with biobrick standard assembly in mind. This RBS has not been explicitly measured for expression rate using fluorescence or B-Gal assay.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64021
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a secretion chaperone from the Salmonella Type III Secretion System (T3S). SicA is required for secretion of sipC protein or sipC tagged heterologous proteins. SicA also functions as a component of a positive feedback loop involving the sicA promoter and invF. For more information see Temme et al in the reference section.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with biobrick standard assembly in mind.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the natural RBS from the sicA chaperone (BBa_J6021) in the Salmonella Type III Secretion System.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Widmaier
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was not designed with standard biobrick assembly in mind.
